Problem 2: Tree Boundary Traversal ğŸŒ³

Problem Description:

Given a binary tree, return its boundary traversal in this order:

ğŸ”¹ Left Boundary: Nodes from root to leftmost leaf (excluding leaves).

 ğŸ”¹ Leaf Nodes: All leaf nodes from left to right.

 ğŸ”¹ Reverse Right Boundary: Nodes from the rightmost leaf back to the root (excluding the root).



Approach:

1ï¸âƒ£ Tree Traversals:

 â€¢ DFS Traversal for left boundary (excluding leaves).

 â€¢ Inorder Traversal to collect all leaf nodes.

 â€¢ DFS Traversal for the right boundary (stored in reverse order).

2ï¸âƒ£ Steps:

 â€¢ Start from the root, traverse the left boundary.

 â€¢ Collect all leaf nodes using an inorder traversal.

 â€¢ Traverse the right boundary and store it in reverse order.



